{
  "stem": "2353.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A year ago, I was called undesirable, inferior, you know, by the Nazis, and all of a sudden I was supposed to be on the German Olympic team.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So when I got back, there was no place for me to train.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was not allowed in the stadium, of course, and it was a pretty, pretty rough time.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I wasn't allowed to compete with the Germans, but three or four times in those two years, I was asked to come to an Olympic training camp where I met all the, the other hopefuls, and I always did better than they did.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And whenever there was a bad press in the United States in-- about discrimination in Germany, I would always be allowed to compete someplace.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And if you can imagine what it feels like to compete in the Adolf Hitler Stadium in front of only non-Jewish people, who most of them wanted to, you know, get at me maybe.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] They didn't have very nice thoughts about me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What is this Jew doing there?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And when I beat all the Germans, that was even worse.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I was always afraid.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I mean, I was afraid day and night that something was going to happen to me.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The reason why I was put on the German Olympic team was that the Americans, the French, the English, they all wanted to boycott the 1936 Olympics in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They said there's discrimination going on, and we're not coming unless you promise-- the Germans, you know, have to promise that there won't be no discrimination, and that's how I landed on the German Olympic team.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was to token Jew, the only Jew, the only Jewish athlete.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
